Headline RoundupMarch 14th, 2024

England Bans Prescription of Puberty Blockers to Children

LGBTQ Issues, Transgender Issues, Gender, Puberty Blockers, United Kingdom, Gender Identity, World, Culture War

Summary from the AllSides News Team

Englands National Health Service has banned the prescription of puberty blockers for children under 18 at gender identity clinics.

The Details: The NHS accepted proposals to stop the practice in 2022 following a review led by Dr. Hilary Cass, that found gaps in evidence around the safety and effectiveness of the drugs. The decision confirms an interim policy established last year after a public consultation reigned in the legality of the drugs to use under exceptional circumstances or research trials only. Going forward, doctors can still apply to have them approved for patients on a case-by-case basis.

For Context: Presently, there is only one gender identity facility for young people in England. According to Wikipedia, puberty blockers have also been banned in thirteen U.S. states: Utah, Idaho, Montana, North Dakota, South Dakota, Iowa, Indiana, Kentucky, Mississippi, Florida, West Virginia, Tennessee, and Oklahoma. 

Key Quotes: Health minister, Maria Caulfield, said, We have always been clear that children's safety and wellbeing [are] paramount, so we welcome this landmark decision by the NHS. Ending the routine prescription of puberty blockers will help ensure that care is based on evidence, expert clinical opinion, and is in the best interests of the child.

How The Media Covered It: The Telegraph (Lean Right bias) labeled puberty blockers as controversial and elevated the landmark significance of the decision. The Guardian (Lean Left bias) included a perspective from the LGBT rights organization Stonewall.
